  <exploitedBy_exapmle rdf:resource="#Angriffsversuche, Netzengpaesse oder absehbare Ausfaelle nicht fruehzeitig erkannt werden."/>
  <description rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">An essential function of automation systems is to monitor operating states of the system being automated. For example, warnings (e.g., exceeding fill levels) and technical parameters (e.g., temperature, valve position) are usually monitored. In contrast, the supporting IT infrastructure is often not monitored. If unusual or security-relevant events are not or only insufficiently monitored, attack attempts, network bottlenecks, or foreseeable failures cannot be detected early.</description>
</owl:NamedIndividual>

